🚀 Project Overview: Mission Management System
-----------------------------------------------
The Mission Management System is a multi-layered ASP.NET Core Web API application designed using the N-Tier Architecture approach. 

It facilitates efficient management and organization of missions, user roles, and related data operations in a structured and scalable manner.

This system demonstrates the use of clean coding principles, separation of concerns, and reusable architecture — ideal for real-world enterprise applications.


📦 Key Components:
-------------------
Mission.Api – The Web API layer that exposes RESTful endpoints to clients.

Mission.Entities – Contains entity classes and database schema definitions.

Mission.Repositories – Handles data access logic using Entity Framework Core.

Mission.Services – Implements business logic and interfaces between the API and Repositories.

Mission.sln – The main Visual Studio solution file for managing and building the entire project.


🛠️ Technologies Used:
---------------------
ASP.NET Core (.NET 8)

Entity Framework Core

C#

PostgreSQL or SQL Server (pluggable via configuration)

REST APIs

Visual Studio 2022
